title: New submarine festival kicks off this weekend in Manitowoc
text:
New submarine festival kicks off this weekend in Manitowoc Jul 8, 2015, 7:37am CDT Share Save Article The city of Manitowoc will kick off its first annual submarine festival this weekend, and no, it's not about sandwiches. Sub Fest is a three-day celebration of the city's rich maritime history that includes the production of 28 submarines during World War II. Originally conceived as a submarine-related film festival, the concept grew to include music, art and activities in downtown Manitowoc. The festival's inaugural theme is World War II and it will feature a showing of the movie "Run Silent, Run Deep" introduced by actor Jim Bates from the film. Other activities include tours of the USS Cobia, a fleet submarine moored in Manitowoc similar to the subs produced in that city for the war, a submarine-inspired art exhibit and, well, a sub-eating contest. Events will take place at the Capitol Civic Centre, Wisconsin Maritime Museum and Rahr-West Art Museum. Those organizations joined with the Manitowoc County Historical Society and the Manitowoc Area Visitor and Convention Bureau to put on the event.
